[gd_resource type="Resource" script_class="HandbookPage" load_steps=2 format=3]

[ext_resource type="Script" path="res://resources/HandbookPage.gd" id="1_page"]

[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_page")
page_id = "procedures"
title = "SOP: STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURES"
content = "[b][color=#006CFF]THE GOLDEN RULE[/color][/b]
[b]VERIFY BEFORE ACTION[/b]. Always [color=cyan]SCAN[/color] a host to confirm infection before using the [color=red]ISOLATE[/color] command. Skipping this step on [b]CRITICAL ASSETS[/b] causes massive service outages and severe [b]Integrity Penalties[/b].

[b][color=#006CFF]RESOLUTION STRATEGIES[/color][/b]
• [b]COMPLIANT[/b]: Full evidence gathered. [i](+Integrity, -Risk)[/i]. Required for all training and high-severity cases.
• [b]EFFICIENT[/b]: Rapid closure. [i](-Integrity, +Risk)[/i]. Use only when the queue is overflowing. Risks missing the [b]Kill Chain[/b].
• [b]EMERGENCY[/b]: Immediate override. [i](--Integrity, +++Risk)[/i]. Use only during catastrophic outbreaks.

[b][color=#006CFF]TECHNICAL GLOSSARY[/color][/b]
• [b]IP Address[/b]: The digital street address of a computer on our network.
• [b]SIEM[/b]: 'Security Information and Event Management'. Our digital CCTV system.
• [b]Kill Chain[/b]: The sequence of steps an attacker takes. Stopping them early saves work later.
• [b]Phishing[/b]: Digital social engineering used to steal credentials or plant malware."
